snippet.textDisplay:
English translation for international viewers:
A stream of joy flows through the world.
Its nectar spills, filling the endless sky.
The sun and the moon sip and relish it.
It keeps the eternal flame lit.
Swept by its waves, the earth is fulfilled.
Today, why confine yourself within?
Why remain absorbed in self?
Look around with an open mind,
Forget all your trivial sorrows,
Fill your empty life with love.

- Translated by Shailesh Parekh


Another translation:

Flowing the stream of bliss across the world,
Divine potion spills day and night throughout the endless sky.
Drinks sun, moon reverently open-handed,
It assures ever-glowing of the endless halo,
The earth, saturated with life and radiance.
Why stay aloof, down with your spirit,
What makes you submerged in thoughts of meagre interests?
Open up your soul, look around,
Ignore miseries trivial,
Pack your empty life with love.

- Translated by Anjan Ganguly
